Defendant Tabatha Lee Comas in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  

Defendant sentenced to serve 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  Letter of apology to Family Dollar;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service;
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $600.00 to Family Dollar or, if not paid, conver to a civil judgment;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
